Well you could ask for an itemized receipt and dispute charges. Often times when you ask for an itemized receipt they'll remove charges anyway because they don't want you to see that the hospital charged you $30 for a Tylenol. You can also ask the debt collector what information was shared with them concerning the debt and you want a copy of whatever legal documentation they have that you signed allowing the hospital to share your medical info. Realistically they won't and can't do anything. They aren't loan sharks. They'll just keep sending bills to your house. Pay it or don't. Worse thing that will happen is it reflects poorly on your credit for seven years but it seems like you're poor and probably don't have credit anyway so who cares?
